@page "/guide"

<div class="container mt-5 p-2">
    <div class="card shadow-sm rounded-4 mx-auto p-2 border-0" style="max-width: 600px;">
        <h6 class="text-muted mb-4"><i class="bi bi-arrow-left me-2"></i>Inspection Guide</h6>

        <section class="mb-4">
            <h6 class="fw-bold">Introduction</h6>
            <p>This guide is designed to help you understand how to use the app to complete an inspection. The app has been built to be flexible and can be used in a variety of different ways depending on your needs.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-4">
            <h6 class="fw-bold">How to Use This Guide</h6>
            <p>We recommend that you read through the entire guide before starting your first inspection. You can also refer back to it at any time.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-4">
            <h6 class="fw-bold">Step 1: Choose Your Inspection Type</h6>
            <p>When you start a new inspection, you will be asked to choose an inspection type. You can choose from a variety of pre-built templates or create your own.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-4">
            <h6 class="fw-bold">Step 2: Add Rooms & Items</h6>
            <p>The next step is to add rooms and items. You can do this by either scanning a barcode or adding them manually.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-4">
            <h6 class="fw-bold">Step 3: Start Inspecting</h6>
            <p>Once you have added all the rooms and items, you can start inspecting. You can take photos, record videos, and add comments as you go.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-4">
            <h6 class="fw-bold">Step 4: Review & Share</h6>
            <p>When you are finished, you can review the report, make any final changes, and share it with your client.</p>
        </section>

        <div class="d-grid">
            <button class="btn rounded-pill fw-semibold text-white" style="background-color:#1c2e41">Start Inspection</button>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
